.TH "i40e_add_ethtool_stats" 9 "i40e_add_ethtool_stats" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
i40e_add_ethtool_stats \- copy stats into ethtool supplied buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "i40e_add_ethtool_stats
.BI "(data "  ","
.BI "pointer "  ","
.BI "stats "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "data" 12
ethtool stats buffer
.IP "pointer" 12
location where stats are stored
.IP "stats" 12
static const array of stat definitions
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Macro to ease the use of __i40e_add_ethtool_stats by taking a static
constant stats array and passing the \fBARRAY_SIZE\fP. This avoids typos by
ensuring that we pass the size associated with the given stats array.

The parameter \fIstats\fP is evaluated twice, so parameters with side effects
should be avoided.
